===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|bergamote|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|bergamotta|lang=it}}; probably a corruption of {{etyl|tr|en}} {{term|bey armudu||a lord's pear|lang=tr}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{botany}} A tree of the orange family ({{taxlink|Citrus bergamia|species}}), having a roundish or pear-shaped fruit, from the rind of which an essential oil of delicious odor is extracted, much prized as a perfume. Also, the fruit. 
# {{botany}} Either of two species of the mint family (Europe: {{taxlink|Mentha aquatica|species}}, variety ''[[glabratus#Latin|glabrata]]''; America: {{taxlink|Monarda didyma|species}}).
# The essence or perfume made from the fruit.
# A variety of pear.
#: {{rfquotek|Johnson}}
# A variety of snuff perfumed with bergamot.
#* {{rfdate}} {{w|William Cowper}}
#*: ''The better hand . . . gives the nose its '''bergamot'''.

